semantischer Bindungstheorien in deutscher Sprache.  aIn its versatilility the German dative is a poorly understood area of grammatical research. This study develops the first unified and explicitly formal theory of the free dative voice in the German language. The central argument is that every free dative functions as an antecedent of a reflexive diathesis. Traditional dative types include the possessive dative, the dativus (in)commode, and the dativus iudicantis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman language -- Case. 0aGerman languagexCase. 4aBindungstheorie (Linguistik). 4aDativ. 4aDiathese (Linguistik). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aBinding Theory.  aDative Case.  aVoice (Grammar).08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103805690 cprintz978311034760940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034773940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110347739423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110347739/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2014